Class NoSuchBeanDefinitionException

  • java.lang.Object
    • java.lang.Throwable

  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    Serializable
    Direct Known Subclasses:
    NoUniqueBeanDefinitionException

    public class NoSuchBeanDefinitionException
extends BeansException
    Exception thrown when a BeanFactory is asked for a bean instance for which it cannot find a definition.
    Author:
    Rod Johnson, Juergen Hoeller
    See Also:
    BeanFactory.getBean(String), BeanFactory.getBean(Class), Serialized Form

        public int getNumberOfBeansFound()
